    "excerpt": "Dean Village (from dene, meaning ‘deep valley’) is a former village immediately northwest of the city centre of Edinburgh, Scotland. It was known as the “Water of Leith Village” and was the centre of a successful grain milling area for more than 800 years. At one time there were no fewer than eleven working mills there, driven by the strong currents of the Water of Leith.  From Wikipedia",
    "content": "<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Dean Village</strong> (from <em>dene</em>, meaning ‘<em>deep valley</em>’) is a former village immediately northwest of the city centre of Edinburgh, Scotland. It was known as the “Water of Leith Village” and was the centre of a successful grain milling area for more than 800 years. At one time there were no fewer than eleven working mills there, driven by the strong currents of the Water of Leith.</p>\n\n  <p class=\"blockquote-footer\">From <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dean_Village\">Wikipedia</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>That was a blockquote with a footer added via kramdown. See <a href=\"https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/content/typography/\">Bootstrap Typography</a> \nto understand <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">.blockquote-footer</code> class.\n<img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Well_Court%2C_Dean_Village%2C_Edinburgh_%2844485996381%29.jpg/800px-Well_Court%2C_Dean_Village%2C_Edinburgh_%2844485996381%29.jpg\" alt=\"Dean Village\" /></p>\n",
